content:
@WG-prioritization/alerts issue #32976 has been requested for prioritization.

Procedure

  • Priority?
  • Regression?
  • Notify people/groups?
  • Needs I-nominated?
Hm, someone used prioritize command for this issue but I don't think we should do?

If the intent of this comment https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/32976#issuecomment-714251021 is to draw attention to this issue, maybe a I-nominate? But the agenda for this week looks already packed, I think it may slip anyway to next week
I think this should be nominated for T-lang (i.e. not T-compiler), shouldn't it?
ah you're right. I don't remember if T-lang make use of the nomination label :thinking: how is an issue usually brought to the T-lang meeting?

apiraino [said](https://rust-lang.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/245100-t-compiler.2Fwg-prioritization.2Falerts/topic/I-prioritize.20.2332976.20Tracking.20issue.20for.20.23.5Bcfg(target_has_ato.E2.80.A6/near/214162848):

ah you're right. I don't remember if T-lang make use of the nomination label :thinking: how is an issue usually brought to the T-lang meeting?

they also use I-nominate AFAIK, the nominated issues and PRs are discussed in the triage meeting, see https://rust-lang.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/213817-t-lang/topic/triage.20meeting/near/213072813 for example

thank you, much clearer now :-)
Will change labels accordingly -T-compiler +T-lang -I-prioritize +I-nominate
